        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "A rare genetic autoinflammatory syndrome characterized by early-onset of repeated episodes of fever nodular neutrophil-rich panniculitis arthralgia and lipodystrophy. Additional reported features include diarrhea failure to thrive lymphadenopathy and vasculitis. Laboratory examination may reveal elevated serum C-reactive protein and leukocytosis with neutrophilia in the absence of infection."
        },
